⭐ DOCUMENT 4 — Safe Use Guide for the IP Continuity Watermark (Rewritten)
Title:
Safe Use Guide for the IP Continuity Watermark

Body:
The IP Continuity Watermark is a public‑safe badge designed to help creators signal authorship, establish continuity, and 
participate in a 
global, creator‑driven protection network.

By using this graphic even once, you are declaring that:

you want your creative work to be protected through the compounding power of continuity, and

you voluntarily choose to have your watermarked work recognized as part of the public continuity layer of the Public Vault.

Using the badge does not expose your private vault or private data. It only connects the specific watermarked work to the public
continuity record.
